Address: 110 S Main St, Ann Arbor, MI 48104
Description: Chic, high-ceilinged wine bar with exposed-brick walls offers 150 wines & a New American menu.

parking: Somewhat difficult to find a space

summary.snippet: "Lovely atmosphere, incredible service and top notch food and drinks."
"Great place for meeting and having a variety of small plates or a larger meal."
"We both ordered the seared salmon served with a very flavorful corn salad."

most_relevant.description: Vinology is one of my favorite intimate wedding venues in the area. The food is fabulous and the bubble room is perfect for an intimate wedding ceremony and reception. All of my couples rave about their experiences here! ig: @chelseabphoto

Phenomenal meal! Maya was amazing. I would have to call this a top 5 lifetime restaurant meal! We had the 2018 Calon Ségur with baked brie, short rib tagliatelle, and filet with out of this world mushrooms. Dessert was barolo with flour less chocolate brownie. O.M.G. 10+/10 !!!

Great atmosphere. Very relaxing. First time going there.. Met my siblings with there spouses there for a after holiday get together. Food was great. Waitress was very attentive. If you have never been.You should try it. It is a wine house. Had a great time.

Excellent restaurant for fine dining.  Have been here half a dozen times or so in the last year.  Definitely enjoy sitting at the bar and having a nice glass of wine.  Will occasionally have dinner and its always excellent.  Most recently had the pasta with a short rib meat sauce.  Followed by one of the best chocolate mousses I’ve had in a long time.  Looking forward to returning soon.

We had our wedding ceremony and reception in 2023. I couldn't recommend this venue more for a small wedding! We rented out the whole lower level for our 50 person wedding reception. I would not recommend this venue if you had anymore than 50 people as it is an intimate space. The food was delicious and we received so many compliments! As for parking, we happened to get married the same day as a home football game but didn't have any issues with parking in the street and nearby lots. All communication is through an online portal and our coordinator was very responsive.

Went for restaurant week and was somewhat disappointed. Maybe I would have had a better experience if I ordered something off of their normal menu. The Matzo Ball Gumbo had an intrusive flavor and was overall okay. The Fatoosh was just a regular salad, nothing crazy. The Braised American Lamb had an extremely strong lamb aroma but had amazing texture. The desserts carried the meal fasho.

We went here for lunch on weekend. The foods were delicious but with a small portion. The shakshuka was smooth and well mixed with the spinach. Fancy restaurant tho, gotta wait for a long time for dishes.

I have been here several times over the years.  This last time was a bit underwhelming.  The dish I had was good.  The scallops were great if small.  Others in my group found the food to be lackluster and a bit disappointing.  The choices seem to be less than before too.  Or maybe we are just in between menus.
